    "recipeIngredient": [
        "4 (6-ounce, 1-inch-thick) boneless, center-cut pork chops",
        "1 teaspoon kosher salt",
        "1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper",
        "6 tablespoons light brown sugar",
        "1/4 cup lower-sodium soy sauce ",
        "1/4 cup water",
        "1 large garlic clove, grated or minced",
        "1/2 teaspoon grated fresh ginger",
        "1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper ",
        "2 tablespoons vegetable oil",
        "Thinly sliced scallions, for garnish, optional"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/VnvJ9APLuVb1zZhUmU6A0N1_iGg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Glazed-Pork-Chops-METHOD-a97593c77c8c4526947163a989b2b140.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Dry brine the pork: Pat the pork chops dry with paper towels and season evenly with the salt and black pepper. Let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/2Epz90RhjgpzDMXTiB5r5VChGgc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Glazed-Pork-Chops-METHOD-2-03ee99c20bcc44039cfe78f86a0feeb2.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Meanwhile, make the glaze: Whisk together the brown sugar, soy sauce, water, garlic, ginger, and red pepper in a medium bowl until combined and the sugar is dissolved."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/n1q9DiVRfSykwzx4OmousznUL1s=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Glazed-Pork-Chops-METHOD-3-cefc70bdb19742c3b0e45e5283f587df.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Cook the pork chops: Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until it ripples across the pan when you tilt it. Add the seasoned pork chops and cook until browned on both sides and a thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the pork chops registers 135°F, 4 to 5 minutes per side, reducing the heat if pork darkens too quickly. Transfer to a plate."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/KakgO0RgYtL1U763aRWAUfkhyRU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Glazed-Pork-Chops-METHOD-5-01a1596dd9914874b3f682329742c92f.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Make the glaze: Reduce the heat to medium. Add the glaze and bring to a boil. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 4 minutes. "
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/zSw4hcavmZSteX7y6ZMc82LEZBY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Glazed-Pork-Chops-LEAD-3-7a9f8816b3954684ba06517846861f7e.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Glaze the pork chops: Return the pork chops and add any accumulated juices to the pan. Cook, basting pork chops with sauce, until the sauce thickens to a glaze consistency, coats the pork chops, and a thermometer inserted into the thickest portion of pork registers 145°F, 3 to 4 minutes.  Remove from the heat. Garnish with scallions and serve drizzled with any remaining glaze.  Store leftovers tightly wrapped or in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 4 days. Love the recipe? Leave us stars and a review below!"
        }
    ],
